Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Thasian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, micaceous, strong orange-brown. Rectangular stamp with uncertain symbol, double struck.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 8. Name Deinopas. Compare Ch. Tchokev, The Athenian Agora xxxvii, 143, no. 200.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0024)
